Install PostgreSQL on Ubuntu

1. Execute the following command to create the file repository configuration:
	
	sudo sh -c 'echo "deb http://apt.postgresql.org/pub/repos/apt $(lsb_release -cs)-pgdg main" > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/pgdg.list'

2. Import the repository signing key:

	wget --quiet -O - https://www.postgresql.org/media/keys/ACCC4CF8.asc | sudo apt-key add -

3. Update the package list:
	
	sudo apt-get update

4. Install the latest version of PostgreSQL:

	sudo apt-get install postgresql

	Note: If you want to install a specific version, you can use postgresql-version instead of postgresql. For example, to install PostgreSQL version 12, you use the following command:
	
		sudo apt-get install postgresql-12


It will take few minutes to download and install the PostgreSQL.
